trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.Activities.NativeActivity> is provided access to the advanced capabilities of the WF runtime via NativeActivityContext, which is passed as a parameter to the activityâ€™s <xref:System.Activities.NativeActivity.Execute%2A> method.
Aborts the current workflow instance during runtime.
Aborts the current workflow instance during runtime for the specified reason.
The error that caused the workflow to abort.
Aborts the specified instance of a <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> child activity.
A child of the currently executing <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
Aborts the specified instance of a <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> child activity for the specified reason.
A child of the currently executing <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
The error that caused the child activity to abort.
Cancels the specified child activity instance.
A child of the currently executing <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
Causes an early completion of all the child activities of an executing <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
Creates a point at which a <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> can passively wait to be resumed.

Creates the point at which a <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> can passively wait to be resumed and schedules the specified method to execute when notification of the resume operation completes.
The method to be called when a notification signals resumption of the <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
Creates the point, with the specified name, at which a <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> can passively wait to be resumed.
A bookmark that includes the name of the bookmark.

Creates the point at which a <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> can passively wait to be resumed, with the specified method to execute when notification of the resume operation completes and with the specified option that governs how the bookmark is used during the execution of the current <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
Bookmark callbacks can operate without bookmark options but bookmark options must always be paired with a callback because the options do not apply in situations where there is no callback method.
The method to be called when a notification signals resumption of the <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
An enumerated setting that governs how the bookmark operates in relation to other threads during the execution of the current <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
A bookmark that includes the callback method and the bookmark execution option.

Creates the point at which a <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> can passively wait to be resumed, with the specified name and with the specified method to execute when notification of the resume operation completes.
The method to be called when a notification signals resumption of the <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
A bookmark that includes the name of the bookmark and the callback method.

Creates the point at which a <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> can passively wait to be resumed with the specified name, the specified method to execute when notification of the resume operation completes, and the specified option that governs how the bookmark is used during the execution of the current <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
Bookmark callbacks can operate without bookmark options but bookmark options must always be paired with a callback because the options do not apply in situations where there is no callback method.
The method to be called when a notification signals resumption of the <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
The bookmark options that govern how the bookmark is used during the execution of the current <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
A bookmark that includes the name of the bookmark, the callback method, and the bookmark execution option.

Creates the point at which a <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> can passively wait to be resumed with the specified name, the specified method to execute when notification of the resume operation completes, and the specified scope of the bookmark.
Bookmark callbacks can operate without bookmark options but bookmark options must always be paired with a callback because the options do not apply in situations where there is no callback method.
The method to be called when a notification signals resumption of the <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
An identifier applied to a group of bookmarks that operate under the same protocol during a workflow runtime.
A bookmark that includes the name of the bookmark, the callback method, and the scope of the bookmark.

Creates the point at which a <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> can passively wait to be resumed with the specified name, the specified method to execute when notification of the resume operation completes, the specified scope of the bookmark, and the specified option that governs how the bookmark is used during the execution of the current <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
Bookmark callbacks can operate without bookmark options but bookmark options must always be paired with a callback because the options do not apply in situations where there is no callback method.
The method to be called when a notification signals resumption of the <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
An identifier applied to a group of bookmarks that operate under the same protocol during a workflow runtime.
The bookmark options that governs how the bookmark is used during the execution of the current <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
A bookmark that includes the name of the bookmark, the callback method, the scope of the bookmark, and the bookmark execution option.
Gets the bookmark scope associated with the root of the workflow.
Returns a collection of the child activities for the current <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
A generic read-only collection of child <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> objects.
Returns the value of the specified variable in the current <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> instance.
The variable whose value is being retrieved during execution of the current <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> instance.
The value of the specified variable.
Gets or sets a value that indicates whether the currently executing <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> instance is to be canceled.

<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the currently executing <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> instance is to be canceled; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
Designates the currently executing <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> instance as canceled.
Gets an object that handles properties for execution of the current <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivityContext"></xref>.
An object that handles execution properties.
Removes all the bookmarks associated with the currently executing <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> instance.
Removes the specified bookmark from the currently executing <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> instance.
A point at which a <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> instance can passively wait to be resumed.
<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the bookmark was removed; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
Removes the bookmark with the specified name.
<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the bookmark was removed; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
Removes the bookmark with the specified name and the specified bookmark scope.
The unique GUID identifier for a group of <xref href="System.Activities.Bookmark"></xref> objects that are categorized as operating under the same protocol.
<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the bookmark was removed; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
A point at which a <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> can passively wait to be resumed.
The information related to the resumption of a bookmark.
The outcome of the attempt to resume <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> operation at the point of the bookmark.

Schedules for execution a specified <xref href="System.Activities.ActivityAction"></xref> that has no parameters, and that bookmarks the specified callback locations where the parent process resumes upon completion of the <xref href="System.Activities.ActivityAction"></xref>.
An action that executes when a specific event occurs in the parent activity.
A bookmark that indicates where the parent activity execution resumes upon completion of the <xref href="System.Activities.ActivityAction"></xref>.
A bookmark that indicates where the parent activity execution resumes if an error causes the termination of the <xref href="System.Activities.ActivityAction"></xref>.
A new instance of an activity action.
Schedules the specified <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> child activity for execution.
A child activity that is triggered by an event that occurs in the execution of a parent <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.

Schedules the specified <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> child activity for execution using the specified completion callback location where the parent process resumes upon completion of the activity.
A child activity that is triggered by an event that occurs in the execution of a parent <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
A bookmark that indicates where the parent activity execution resumes upon completion of the <xref href="System.Activities.ActivityAction"></xref>.

Schedules the specified <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> child activity for execution using the specified fault callback location where the parent process resumes when the activity enters the faulted state.
A child activity that is triggered by an event that occurs in the execution of a parent <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
A bookmark that indicates where the parent activity execution resumes if an error causes the termination of the <xref href="System.Activities.ActivityAction"></xref>.

Schedules the specified <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> child activity for execution and bookmarks the specified callback locations where the parent process resumes upon completion of the child activity.
A child activity that is triggered by an event that occurs in the execution of a parent <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref>.
A bookmark that indicates where the <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> execution resumes upon completion of the <xref href="System.Activities.ActivityAction"></xref>.

A bookmark that indicates where the <xref href="System.Activities.NativeActivity"></xref> execution resumes if an error causes the termination of the <xref href="System.Activities.ActivityAction"></xref>.
Pushes the callback method for an activity into the work item pool.
The callback method to which an activity returns when the specified activity action completes.
A dictionary list of activity argument names and values.
A bookmark that indicates where the parent activity execution resumes upon completion of the <xref href="System.Activities.ActivityAction"></xref>.
A bookmark that indicates where the parent activity execution resumes if an error causes the termination of the <xref href="System.Activities.ActivityAction"></xref>.
Assigns the specified value object to the specified variable object.
A variable object without a specified type that can be assigned a value object.
An object without a specified type that can be assigned to a variable object.
Adds an activity tracking record to the current workflow instance.
The data sent to tracking participants when tracked events occur.
